<%= page_title('➜ ringo') %>

<div id="am-main">
  <ul id="am-settings-nav" class="nav nav-tabs">
    <li><a href="/settings">Settings</a></li>
    <li class="active"><a href="#">Install Bookmarklet</a><li>
  </ul>

  <div class="hidden-phone">
    <h4 class="span12">
      Import web pages with one click
    </h4>
    <div class="span4">
      <div>
        The <tt>ringo</tt> bookmarklet enables you to save any web page to <tt>ringo</tt> with just one click! Once you've imported a web page, you can highlight bits of it and incorporate them into your questions.
      </div>
      <br />
      <div>
        To install the <tt>ringo</tt> bookmarklet, drag this little chicklet...
      </div>
      <br />
      <div id="am-bookmarklet-well" class="span2 well">
        <a id="am-bookmarklet" class="btn btn-small" href="<%= RailsBookmarklet.compile_invocation_script(create_via_bookmarklet_selections_url, {
          :error => 'Uh-oh, something went wrong.',
          :params => {
            "uri" => "'+encodeURIComponent(d.location)+'"
          }
        }) %>">➜ ringo</a>
      </div>

      <div style="clear: both">
        ...to the bookmarks bar in your browser. Then, whenever you're on a page you'd like to save to <tt>ringo</tt>, click the <span id="am-bookmarklet" class="btn btn-small">➜ ringo</span> button in your bookmarks bar, and the current page will be imported into your <tt>ringo</tt> account.
      </div>

      <p>&nbsp;</p>
    </div>

    <div class="span4">
      <%= image_tag "bookmarklet-in-bookmarks-bar.png" %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="am-install-bookmarklet-on-phone" class="visible-phone">
    <h4>
      Import web pages with one click
    </h4>
    <p>
      The <tt>ringo</tt> bookmarklet enables you to save any web page to <tt>ringo</tt> with just one click! Once you've imported a web page, you can highlight bits of it and incorporate them into your questions. Follow the steps below to install the <tt>ringo</tt> bookmarklet on your phone.
    </p>

    <ol>
      <li>Bookmark this page.</li>
      <li>
        Tap on the field below and press down until some text is selected in a blue overlay. Adjust this blue overlay to cover all the code in the field, then click 'Copy'.
        <br />
        <p id="am-bookmarklet-code" class="well"><%= RailsBookmarklet.compile_invocation_script(create_via_bookmarklet_selections_url, {
            :error => 'Uh-oh, something went wrong.',
            :params => {
              "uri" => "'+encodeURIComponent(d.location)+'"
            }
          }) %>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>Open your bookmarks by clicking the book button at the bottom of your browser.</li>
      <li>Click the 'Edit' button on the lower left.</li>
      <li>Click on the '➜ ringo' bookmark.</li>
      <li>Click on the field where it says 'https://ringo.com/install-bookmarklet'.</li>
      <li>Click the circled 'x' at the right end of that field to clear it.</li>
      <li>Hold down on this field until you see the 'Paste' button.</li>
      <li>Click 'Paste'.</li>
      <li>Click the 'Done' button on the lower right.</li>
      <li>Click the 'Done' button on the lower left.</li>
      <li>Click the 'Done' button on the upper right.</li>
    </ol>

    <p>Now, whenever you're on a page you'd like to save to <tt>ringo</tt>, click the book button at the bottom of your browser, then click the <br />'➜ ringo' bookmark, and the current page will be imported into your <tt>ringo</tt> account.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  </div>
</div>
